Beachcomber smiles, "Yes, somehow I already had that feeling, that you
were capable I mean. Cliffjumper wouldnt of asked if he didnt feel the
same way." Beachcomber saying, as he noted the bow. It must have been
some kind of custom he was not used to. He recorded it. Cliffjumper
finished shaking. "Well we have a kid in our group, who is still at
Maximal city. We'll have to go back and get him, and resign as
Maximals." He said with confidence.
